{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"faf166d9-5e3f-41eb-862c-8566331eb4dd","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project too:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator does a \"contains\" match, while `=` does an exact match. You can also use `DisplayName~ReportExporterTests` if the other filters don't work with your test framework.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c16903be-da56-4d30-914f-2f6ebc284ac9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly without needing to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":204,"requestId":"481F:FD676:7C74CC:8FBB78:69FBE8E7"},"id":"fe47295f-bd2e-4bfb-8322-44309c383a42","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:20:44.094Z","parentId":"11f03617-c9f6-48cb-8695-ce509c70aab4"}
